params.masterTokenAddress_: The address of the master token.
params.ownerAddress_: The address of the owner of the new vault.
params.sharesName_: The name for the shares of the vault.
params.sharesSymbol_: The symbol for the shares of the vault.
params.underlyingTokenAddress_: The address of the underlying token.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.vaultImplementation_: The address of the vault implementation.

returns._0: status True if the vault is active, false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.defaultFeeRate_: The new default fee rate to be set.

params.newImplementation_: The address of the new vault implementation.

params.status_: The new status of the vault (active or not).

BASE().notice: The base multiplier for fee calculations, set to 100%.

defaultFeeRate().notice: The default fee rate for the vaults.

deployVault(address,address,address,stri.notice: Deploys a new vault using the beacon proxy.

getVaultImplementationAddress().notice: Returns the current vault implementation address.

getbeaconProxyAddress().notice: Returns the address of the beacon proxy.

initialize(uint256,address).notice: Initializes the registry with the default fee rate and vault implementation.

isVaultActive(address).notice: Checks if a vault is active.

setDefaultFeeRate(uint256).notice: Sets a new default fee rate.

setVaultImplementation(address).notice: Updates the vault implementation in the beacon proxy.

validVaults(address).notice: Mapping to track whether a vault is active.
